<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1293,1497]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Comments: 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[335,490,1401,1425]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="110 - 136" refId="ref40527" refString="Nieser, N. (1968) Notonectidae of Suriname, with additional records of other neotropical species. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 10, 110 - 136." type="journal article" year="1968">Nieser (1968)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Truxal" authorityYear="1953" box="[824,920,1401,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Buenoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[824,920,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">B. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in AM in the distributional list of the species, without a detailed locality. Because no other records from this state were found and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[1094,1248,1437,1461]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="110 - 136" refId="ref40527" refString="Nieser, N. (1968) Notonectidae of Suriname, with additional records of other neotropical species. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 10, 110 - 136." type="journal article" year="1968">Nieser (1968)</bibRefCitation>
did not examine specimens from the Brazilian Amazon, the record is not considered here.
</paragraph>
